leadership_approach|people_process_results_vision|paired|people|process|results|vision|How People-and-Process leadership responds under pressure|This leadership pattern organises the response through People and Process together: combining trust, communication, and shared confidence with structure, sequence, and repeatable standards. Results and Vision keep the pair from becoming too narrow.|This leadership pattern shows up when pressure makes both trust, communication, and shared confidence and structure, sequence, and repeatable standards feel necessary to stabilise the work. The later signals test whether the response also needs clearer outcomes, decisions, and next steps or longer-range direction, future context, and wider meaning.|This leadership pattern protects the work from low trust, poor communication, quiet resistance, and weak shared understanding while adding structure, sequence, and repeatable standards. It narrows when the pair runs ahead of Results and Vision, so strengthen them before the response closes around the top two routes.|active|leadership_approach::people_process_results_vision::paired
leadership_approach|people_process_results_vision|graduated|people|process|results|vision|How a People-led leadership sequence responds under pressure|This leadership pattern follows a clear sequence: People starts the response, Process strengthens it, then Results and Vision add range as the work broadens.|This leadership pattern shows up when pressure rewards a clear order of attention, starting with trust and shared understanding. Each later signal tests whether the response also needs stronger structure, coordination, and repeatable standards, clearer outcomes, decisions, and next steps, or longer-range direction, future context, and wider meaning.|This leadership pattern protects the work by giving leadership attention a sequence from trust, communication, and shared confidence toward longer-range direction and future context. It narrows when Results or Vision arrive too late, so bring them in before the first routes settle the response too early.|active|leadership_approach::people_process_results_vision::graduated
